{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"body":"## Investigation finding — mount fix is necessary but NOT sufficient\n\nThe immediate CI failure IS the missing tickets-store mount (verify-identity exits 2, \"ticket store not found\"). Mount step written (mirrors reconcile-bridge.yml). BUT mounting alone will not make the gate green:\n\n- `rebar fsck` reports **0 signed, 3504 unsigned** events. Authenticated signing was scaffolded (the gate + CLI) but never turned on for writes — no `identity.signing_key` / self-identity configured, and `rebar.toml` has no `[identity]` block.\n- The workflow forces `--require-authenticated` and reads `--since` from the `ENFORCE_SINCE` repo variable, which is **unset** (confirmed via `gh variable get`). So enforcement is on with **no grandfathering** → every in-scope unsigned event fails the gate → guaranteed non-zero exit.\n- Performance: a bounded `--base HEAD~200` scan exceeded 180s locally (29,575 tracker commits / 3504 events); a full `--since \"\"` scan did not complete in 10 min.\n\nConclusion: the gate was enabled in enforcing mode before signing was actually rolled out. Making CI green requires an enforcement-posture decision (advisory-until-signing vs grandfather-all-now + turn signing on), not just the mount. Holding the mount commit pending that decision."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783979030408138001,"uuid":"d8269f87-47d9-4433-afa5-f232b1da0cb2"}